1. What is Android?

Android is an open-source, Linux-based mobile operating system developed by Google for smartphones, tablets, TVs, and wearables.

Key Points:
Based on Linux Kernel
Used to build mobile apps using Java / Kotlin
Apps run inside Android Runtime (ART)
Supports touch-based UI
Features of Android
Open Source – Anyone can modify it
Multitasking – Run multiple apps at once
Custom UI – Widgets, themes, launchers
Connectivity – WiFi, Bluetooth, NFC, 4G/5G
App Framework – Easy app development
Media Support – Audio, video, images
Google Services – Maps, Gmail, Play Store
Security – App sandboxing + permissions
Multi-language support
