2. What is Framework?

A framework is a predefined structure (tools + libraries) that helps developers build applications faster without writing everything from scratch.

Android Framework (Architecture)
5
Layers:
Linux Kernel
Hardware interaction (camera, memory, drivers)
Libraries + Android Runtime (ART)
Core libraries (SQLite, WebKit)
Runs apps efficiently
Application Framework
Activity Manager
Window Manager
Content Providers
View System
Applications
User apps (WhatsApp, Instagram)

👉 Framework gives APIs to interact with lower layers.
