3. Android Activity Life Cycle
6
Definition:

Activity lifecycle = states an activity goes through during its lifetime

Methods:
onCreate()
→ Activity created (UI initialized)
onStart()
→ Activity becomes visible
onResume()
→ User can interact (foreground)
onPause()
→ Partially hidden (incoming call etc.)
onStop()
→ Fully hidden
onDestroy()
→ Activity destroyed
onRestart()
→ Restart after stop
Flow:
onCreate → onStart → onResume
   ↓
onPause → onStop → onDestroy
